column1: This is a historic election and every vote matters. There are long lines at some polling stations but do not give up on exercising your right to vote! The Golden 1 Center arena downtown has the largest capacity for fast voting. 2/2 #Vote2020

Sacramento County elections officials report 10 of the 84 county vote centers are experiencing long lines and long waits including waits of up to two hours at the South Natomas vote center. https://t.co/Yk73Ym3fQe 1/2 #Vote2020

Teachers are essential to our children' success. I applaud teachers for stepping up when CA shifted to distance learning. I am honored that @WeAreCTA has endorsed me as I run for reelection. I will continue to stand up for our teachers schools students and families in Congress

Thank you National Organization for Women (NOW) @NationalNOWPAC for supporting my campaign for reelection in CA-6. I will continue to earn your trust and support by fighting for women’s rights in Congress! #VOTE #Vote2020

I am very proud of the hard work this election cycle by @CA_Dem @CAYoungDems @sacdems  @femdems916 @sacwomendems Harry S Truman Democratic Club of Greater Sacramento and the Sacto Dem Alliance and I am extremely honored to have earned your support. 2/2

Democrats in California and across the nation are working hard this election season to elect Joe Biden and Kamala Harris flip the Senate and expand our majority in the House - in addition to electing Democrats in our state and local races. 1/2
I voted early. However you decide to vote - have a plan and use your voice. Vote. #Vote2020 https://t.co/DDypFBscIu
“...Planned Parenthood Action Fund is proud to endorse Doris Matsui for reelection to Congress.” - Alexis McGill Johnson President and CEO of Planned Parenthood Action Fund 2/2 @PPact @PPActionCA

I will always stand up for women and am so proud to be endorsed by Planned Parenthood Action Fund! @PPact “Doris Matsui is a champion for reproductive rights who fights to make sure comprehensive health care is accessible for everyone...” 1/2
... I look forward to campaigning hard for the Biden-Harris ticket all the way to victory in November. #BidenHarris2020   2/2

I am thrilled with @JoeBiden’s selection of US Senator @KamalaHarris as his running mate. I can think of no one better than CA’s own Kamala Harris to take a new set of values back to the White House. Kamala is a fighter a leader and a friend.... 1/2

Right now there could not be a clearer difference between a true transparent and empathetic leader like Joe Biden and the current occupant in the White House. It’s time for real leadership in the Oval Office and that’s why I am supporting Joe Biden for President. (2/2)

I am proud to endorse my good friend Joe Biden for President. I worked with Joe on including my Excellence in Mental Health Act in his Gun Violence Task Force. He’s been a leader on issues like healthcare climate change infrastructure & protecting women from violence. (1/2)

I want to thank the voters of the 6th CD for once again demonstrating their support during the 2020 Primary. The upcoming election is so important. As we move on to November I want you to know that we will continue to campaign to represent Sacramento values in Congress.
Your Vote is Important. Make your voice heard by casting your ballot! Vote 🗳 Today. https://t.co/HPyOw1d6kG
New! Doris Matsui for Congress Ad - Sacramento Values https://t.co/qbnNlfXDqg via @YouTube
